# Walkthrough: Responsive Dashboard Implementation

We have successfully transitioned the Spectral Soundworks application from a desktop-only layout to a fully responsive, mobile-first experience. This allows for lead management and project tracking across all device form factors.

## Completed Changes

### 1. Global Navigation & Layout
- **Responsive Sidebar**: Transformed the vertical sidebar into a fixed bottom navigation bar (`Bottom Nav`) on mobile devices (`< 768px`).
- **Compact Navbar**: Redesigned the top navigation bar to collapse unnecessary elements on mobile and use flexible searching.
- **Root Layout Optimization**: Removed restrictive `flex` constraints on the `body` and `main` elements, allowing the browser to handle text wrapping and layout scaling naturally without forcing horizontal scrollbars.

### 2. Dashboard & Leads Management
- **Responsive Grids**: Updated the main dashboard and leads directory to use responsive grid systems that stack vertically on mobile.
- **Card Scaling**: Adjusted lead cards and progress bars to use dynamic widths (`w-full`) instead of fixed pixel widths.
- **Typography Scaling**: Dynamically scaled large "Hero" headers throughout the app to prevent text clipping on narrow viewports.

### 3. Lead Discovery & Project Views
- **Lead Discovery**: Added responsive breakpoints to the discovery search configuration and results tables.
- **Lead Details**: Optimized the cinematic artist header for mobile portrait ratios and refactored social/draft cards for better legibility.
- **GlassCard System**: Updated the shared `GlassCard` component with responsive padding (`p-6` mobile vs `p-8` desktop) and grounding (`rounded-3xl` mobile vs `rounded-[48px]` desktop) to ensure nested content remains clear on small screens.

## Verification

### Breakpoint Testing
- **Mobile (375px - 500px)**: Verified that the Bottom Nav is active, headers are scaled, and all grids stack correctly.
- **Tablet (768px)**: Verified that the Sidebar returns to its vertical orientation while the main content remains flexible.
- **Desktop (1440px+)**: Verified that the premium wide-screen layouts remain intact with the original cinematic aesthetic.

> [!TIP]
> You can test these changes live by resizing your current browser window. The sidebar will flip to the bottom once you go below 768px in width.

